# One pkgsrc package origin (category/name) per line. These are the
# packages the other Cross-Platform Action ports get from official pkgsrc
# binary mirrors but that have no prebuilt vax builds.
#
# NOTE: curl is intentionally omitted. It needs openssl, and openssl needs
# perl to build; perl takes far longer than GitHub's 6-hour job limit to
# compile on the emulated VAX and can't resume mid-compile, so it can never
# finish. curl's HTTP-fetch role is already covered by NetBSD base ftp(1).
# rsync is kept but patched (see remote-build.sh) to drop its openssl
# dependency for the same reason.
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
shells/bash
security/sudo
net/rsync
